security and reliability hardening

Security:
- shop_api: require SHOP_API_KEY header on all mutating routes; allowlist PATCH order fields; rollback HELD on append_order failure
- main: verify Telegram X-Telegram-Bot-Api-Secret-Token; fail-closed /jobs/expire when SEPAY_API_KEY missing
- sepay_webhook: fail-closed verify_sepay_auth; secrets.compare_digest
- admin_dashboard: secrets.compare_digest for admin password; prefer x-admin-key header
- admin_services: redact secret and deliver_text in snapshot by default (reveal_secrets=1 opt-in)
- bot_shop: /mail and /2fa restricted to ADMIN_IDS (also block heuristic detector); ADMIN_IDS default empty

Reliability:
- main: deep /health probes Telegram + Sheets; track in-flight payment tasks for graceful shutdown
- sepay_webhook: per-tx_id asyncio.Lock + processed_set for idempotency; cleanup lock after use
- admin_services: normalize stock_code on save; validate price > 0

UX / Ops:
- bot: new /help command; show PENDING/PAID/EXPIRED orders to user with status icons
- backup_manager: exposed via POST /admin/api/backup
- FE: send admin key via x-admin-key header; auto-logout on 401 toast; remove hardcoded service name from sidebar

Cleanup:
- delete legacy bot_shop_lay_tt.py (1.6k LOC dead code)
- delete unused FE components ProductsTable / OrdersTable / StatsCards
- .env.example documents SHOP_API_KEY / TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET / BACKUP_* / ALLOW_PUBLIC_*
